          <p>The introduction of a new entitlement means there will be additional costs for the Exchequer in the form of payments at the statutory rate (currently £156.66). However, this will somewhat be offset by the business contribution to statutory payments. Large employers can reclaim via HMRC 92% of the statutory payments they pay to employees. For smaller employers (defined as those with a National Insurance contributions Bill less £45,000) they can reclaim 103% of the statutory payments they pay to their employees. See box below for further details on how Exchequer costs are calculated. The approach taken is the same as analysis in the Carer’s Leave Impact Assessment. </p>
